tagDescription: LEWIS AND CLARK EXPEDITION History of the expedition of Captains Lewis and Clark 1804-5-6. Reprinted from the edition of 1814, by James K. Kosmer, in two volumes with portraits and maps (Chicago: A.C. McClurg & Co., 1904), 583 and 500 pages; and Gass's Journal of the Lewis and Clark Expedition, by Sergeant Patrick Gass, one of the persons employed in the expedition, reprinted from the edition of 1811 (Chicago: A.C. McClurg & Co., 1904), 298 pages.

CHIPPEWA JOURNAL Anishinabe Enamiad. A monthly journal devoted to the interests of the Franciscan missions among the Ottawa and Chippewa Indians. (Bound in two volumes, volumes 1-14, March 1896-February 1910).
